caption: Love the food, workers, and atmosphere. It was a really nice experience I will definitely be back here👌

Had dinner out front here and it was really top notch. If you're looking for something savory but slightly different, definitely come to Bolinas. I had the edamame hummus (that fresh bread that accompanies it is nothing short of a salty squishy puffy miracle), the chicken bao, and the watermelon ginger frozen margarita, all delicious. Highly recommend everything else on the menu, too!

Favorite spot in BK.  Amazing food, eccentric staff, beautiful space.  Mostly locals so you know it’s legit.  A must-visit if you are in Clinton Hill/Fort Greene.
Nice neighborhood bar. Great burgers 🍔. Come in for drinks and takeout from here at least once a week.

Perfect brunch oasis that takes you west into the Cali-mex world of the central California coast. Delicious, chill, fun vibe, great staff.
Greens and Eggs.  Le best.  A great place to stop for lunch!  A real NYer place.

Always a solid meal. Bao buns, tacos and Porter. Heaven.

I have been coming here for a couple of years, for dinner and drinks.  The food is always amazing, their cheeseburger, fried chicken sandwich really hit the spot.  A huge fan of their version of a pozole, its very light and a favorite comfort food now in the winter months.  They have the loveliest patio in the warmer months.  The service is always outstanding great if you are dining alone or with a friend.  One of the better restaurants in the neighborhood and has always remained consistent in quality.
Get the chicken sandwich!!

Great brunch spot! You MUST start your meal with a biscuit and honey butter — it’s quite possibly one of the best things I’ve ever had. The honey butter is game-changing. I got the Huevos Rancheros and a spin on an Aperol Spritz to drink. This place will be on my brunch list for this Brooklyn area.
Food was really good and plenty vegetarian options. Drinks were really well made and staff knew their alcohol/liqueurs and they had lots of fascinating bottles. Would totally go back.
First time in this very nice neighborhood restaurant and bar. Came for brunch. Very good food. Highly recommend.

Nice friendly service by staff & private accommodations for 22 people. Sauteed greens too salty but dishes sauces, spices & tap ginger ale excellent.
One of my favorite brunch spots bar none. I don't even live in the neighborhood but I keep coming back. That homemade hot sauce is worth the trip alone.

Great neighborhood spot. The back yard is nice.
Nice place, with patio out the back. A little bit pricey for what it is. I had the burger and it could have had a bit more flavour for 18$

Bar Bolinas is an unassuming, simple bar with a great atmosphere, superb food, and quality cocktails. The outdoor patio in the back is a nice reprieve from the city bustle as well. Limited, but good, draft beer options, so go for cocktails. Lastly, the staff is fun, welcoming and personable. Definitely swing by Bar Bolinas if you're in Brooklyn!
I work here and I can say the food is astonishing , decorated plates , classy drinks, and a experience that makes you wanna Kome back!!! Plus there's a back yard !!

So far my company usually orders take out from here, and I just have to say I absolutely love the food from here! Had tried the bigger recently but my absolute love is for the amazing shrimp tacos! 😌 I definitely will definitely stop by to grab drinks and recommend this place!
Rude staff. Terrible service. Good food if you have the patience of a saint.
My favorite community gathering place. Always fresh local ingredients and smiling faces!
Good food and excellent service
Food and drinks are excellent.
It's OK.  Kind of grungesque.  I wanted to like it more.  Service was friendly and the food was filling.  In fairness, I may be too old for places like this
Great food and drinks. Enjoyed our evening!

Has been (and maybe it still can be) a neighborhood gem of ours for the last few years. Returning customers if not bi-weekly, but for sure at least a few times in a month. Last delivery experience was SO bad, we'll definitely never order delivery again. Ordered 1 appetizer and 2 entrees, and delivery was missing one entree and the other entree that was delivered was incorrect, AND missing simple sides (sauces, pickles etc. ). Not sure who the manager was that evening, but clearly not on point with orders that were leaving the restaurant. 1st call: lady picked up, she was friendly, told me she'd call me back with an update, 20 mins later, no call. So I called again, a guy picked up (totally know which server he was by the way he talked and tried to "explain" himself), and basically told me that there was absolutely NOTHING he/restaurant could do about the incorrect order we received and that GrubHub would call me and then I would have then reorder if I wanted the 2nd missing entree. So basically, there went my date night. We shared one incorrectly delivered entree, Grubhub never called me, and I also have no interest in paying the $3.99 delivery fee again when it wasn't my fault to begin with. As much as we have loved and been loyal to Bar Bolinas the last few years, not sure if we want to keep supporting such hospitality in the neighborhood. Last thing we need in the these parts of Brooklyn is more inconsiderate, unhelpful, difficult, rude hipster services. Miss those days when customer service actually meant something in the hospitality world. Now it's sadly rare.

Really good bar in the heart of Brooklyn. It is located in a street with other bars and restaurants.  Didn't plan to stop by but looked so good from the outside that I decided to have a couple of beers while I was on my way to get dinner. The bar is really nice with a great liquor choice. Service really good and nice atmosphere. Good job! I will order food next time!
Have the grilled crispy sourdough. It might be the best thing I have ever eaten. Friendly people, no ice vibe. Try it.

One of our favorite spots in the neighborhood, but their delivery experience is by far the very worst I’ve ever encountered.  They regularly cancel orders after they’re placed with no rhyme or reason.  If the restaurant is not equipped to offer delivery, just don’t do it.  With this being a regular occurrence, it’s certainly a turn-off from actually going there in person anymore, let alone attempting to place another delivery order.

Despite the humble appearance and Brooklyn vibe of "we're too cool to be nice" ...the food will blow your mind! I am convinced that I got contact high on my walk here, because I ate the food like I had crazy munchies. I can't rave enough about the taste, use of flavor, texture and colors. The cooks really make a perfect experience of cuisine.

Great spot! Nice bar for drinks and great garden for outdoor brunch in nice weather. I'd call this place California fusion. American bar with a lot of Mexican influence on their menu. Definately good for small groups offering.

This a busy, cute spot on Myrtle. It looks like the garden would be nice in warmer weather. We enjoyed the German Pancake. It tastes like French toast with apples and was quite delicious. I would have like the eggs with biscuits and sausage gravy to be better. The flavor of the gravy was very nice and peppery. But the over easy eggs were overcooked and the biscuit was very hard as well. It tasted like it may have been made the day before. We were in a rush so I didn't tell the service staff so maybe they would have remade it. We will try this place again.
Good food . ok prices . No life

Very cute spot in Clinton Hill. Get there early before the crowds, as it fills up pretty quickly on the weekend for Brunch. Very family friendly, lots of young children around. Huevos Rancheros were very good, highly recommend. Staff are generally friendly. Worth a visit!
Excellent quality food here. The pozole is just incredible. I often get the nachos to share. They are like 'healthy' nachos because there are vegetables here and there.
Great brunch spot.  Fried chicken sandwich was tasty.  The burger is delicious also

This is my third time here and I was originally referred here for the burger.  It was that burger and the other food menu items that have kept me coming back for more....  The service is pretty chill and easy going and the warm cozy neighborhood atmosphere is perfect for a simple meal or chill date night (pre Netflix)  Get a burger and start with the fried oysters. You'll be glad you did
Good, limited selection of food but good value now for the area
Great food, great atmosphere, super friendly service.
Nice but casual spot which was good for a leisurely backyard brunch with friends. Wasn’t overly crowded on Sunday at 1pm. Burger was really good, kale salad was even better.
The food was good but the bartender and waitstaff were really unfriendly. Definitely wouldn’t recommend it.
This is one of my favorite neighborhood places. I love the food and love the atmosphere!
Great neighborhood staple

$15 for two teeny white people tacos. B health rating. Annoying staff and worse customers. This place is generic Brooklyn mush.

Walked in, politely greeted gentlemen and ladies at the bar and I was promptly seated. Very pleasant interior decor, with decent seating space. The servers seemed... distant and disconnected. Prefering instead to chat up two ladies by the bar. All fine here. There were perhaps ten people in the whole restaurant for late lunch. If this joint is full of life and less mediocre during night than during the day, I would not know. The only expression I could possibly consider when referring to the quality of food is... eh. Nothing extraordinary. The meat within the tacos I have ordered were most definitely not cooked the same day or extremely overcooked. Dried and chewy. Also, a full bar could use a little more than six beer choices.

Food was fantastic! So much flavor in each dish. Loved the pork tacos and nachos! We also had the portobello mushroom burger which was   undescribebly good. You have to give this place a try if you have the opportunity.
Burger, Kale Salad, brunch menu are all good food
Cute place for a casual bite. Great atmosphere, great food, and reasonable prices.
Nice place, friendly staff a little bit pricey though.
Third time there. The food quality is great, deliciously prepared, and has consistently delivered. Plus it is super cute. Highly recommend it.
Really, really good food.  Easy atmosphere.
Great food with reasonable prices. Lovely backyard seating, cozy for late nights.
The food is very delicious!!

Went with a party of 3 for brunch, I really enjoyed the burger but my wife and friend were not as crazy about the chicken sandwich and the breakfast tacos. The cocktails were also a little over priced and not too tasty. It was a fine meal but nothing exceptional.

Friendly staff and good food, pleasant patrons. Sort of my home away from home. One of my favorite restaurants in Brooklyn.

Decent eatery. Fresh food. Good service. Just nothing special.
Not pretentious. Good vibe. Friendly. Great food. 👍🏻

I ate here when it first opened and have frequented the restaurants several times. I want to like the place but as a disabled person my biggest gripe is that the place is not truly ADA compliant after its renovation. Restroom is not wheelchair accessible and there are steps to backyard. The seating for most tables are high stools. It's deceptive to list this place with an accessible entrance only to find that you will have to leave the restaurant and go elsewhere to use a restroom.
Creative dishes, reasonable prices, lots of healthy options.

Easy going feeling with very tasty food. I've had brunch there once and dinner twice and my favorite is the spicy chicken sandwich. Tried the regular too, but the spice is nice if you like flavorful heat.
Best burger around.
Pork belly sandwich.
Excellent. Nice garden seating in back and a wonderful burger.

One of my favorite neighborhood spots. Spicy chicken sandwich and kale salad. Always.  It's always a little busy but not ever packed to the brim at brunch / dinner. Nice, cozy vibe and good drinks as well. Bonus tip: they have a great outdoor seating area in the back when the weather is nice!
Love this place. Great drinks and food. Service is perfect.
Great fresh food and drinks. Love the option to sit outside, or on the enclosed terrace
love this place even though I miss Maggie Brown

Went for brunch. Service was friendly and the food wast tasty. Had a good burger, and a friend had the German pancake, which was very good. Coffee is french press, which I am not a fan of, but free refills.  They open at 10am for brunch, which is nice for early birds.

Went here last night, Had one of the best cocktails ive tasted in a while, very strong "divers wife". Followed by the burger, which was a perfect medium rare, and the best around. Then two desserts to finish off which were unique and delicious, the "hot chocolate" and the "candy cap custard". Tastiest restaurant I've been to in the clinton hill / fort greene area.
We lost a black hat, and they kept it for us to pick up another day. Loved their bloody Mary!
Had some tasty drinks, some lovely conversation and a couple of delicious bites here my last time in Brooklyn.
The happy hour deal of burger,  fries,  and Tecate for 10 bucks is really great.  The burger is dry aged with a yummy bun and pickled onion. Try the sausage bao,  it's too die for.
Great brunch. Biscuits and pancakes are great!!! Like the drinks too
Fried oysters, need I say more? Cozy little spot, in the heart of things.

Quote from the female bar tender with short hair after we asked for another round "I don't want to make another, but I will", hadn't been here for more than 30 minutes and I have heard probably the rudest comment from any sever in my entire life. The lady proceeds to make sarcastic remarks with my friend when she politely asks her to serve our drinks. Five days in Brooklynd and I was just about to say I've never been anywhere with such nice people, way to go and screw that up for a an urban population of a few million short haired chick.

The menu and the food are excellent. The service reflects poor training, a stoner pace, and aimless wandering of at least one of the two servers. Also, the kitchen staff seems unable to multitask in order to get the food for a given table ready within a narrow window of time.
Great cocktails,  great food. Wish I lived a little closer!!!

My first night in Brooklyn, I was invited to Bar Bolinas tor dinner. The food quality, preparation, and service was so outstanding I returned for dinner two additional times in five days adding on guests to share my delight.  You must try the peanuts with cocktails, pasta with chanterelles, kale salad, and whatever seafood they are featuring that night.  The wait staff is also terrific and took the trouble to Fedex my cellphone and glasses to me when I returned home.  As they pointed out, perhaps I really didn't want to leave!  They were so right!
Perfect egg sandwich & beacon. Really like the place and the service.
I really like this place. Relaxed atmosphere, great food. The burger is excellent and the Bolinas salad is one of the best salads I've ever had. Brunch is great, too.
Seriously good in so many ways. Imaginative courses made well and balanced, combined with friendly staff makes for a pretty great restaurant.

Went for the morels and stayed for four more plates! The selection and preparation is unique and well thought out. Atmosphere was perfect for a date night. Looking forward to all the great things to come.
